<a id="notification_setup"></a>
<h2>Setting Up The Notification System</h2>
<p>Notifications are provided through RSS feeds.</p>
<p>Your personal RSS feed is customized based on your liked and disliked post tags. A link to your RSS feed is available from your profile page.</p>
<%= image_tag("support/installation/notification_link.png") %>

<p>To access your personalised RSS feed, you need a feed reader. We provide installation instructons for RSS feed readers below.</p>
<p>
  Jump to feed reader installation:
  <%= link_to "Windows", :anchor => "notification_setup_windows" %>,
  <%= link_to "Mac OS X", :anchor => "notification_setup_mac_os_x" %>
</p>

<a id="notification_setup_windows"></a>
<h3>Windows</h3>

<h4>Omea Reader</h4>
<p class='ui-state-highlight'><span class="ui-icon ui-icon-info" style="float: left; margin-right: .3em;"></span>This guide is written based on Omea Reader version 2.2</p>
<ol>
  <li>Download Omea Reader from <%= link_to 'http://www.jetbrains.com/omea/download/reader.html', 'http://www.jetbrains.com/omea/download/reader.html' %></li>
  <li>Install Omea Reader using the downloaded .exe</li>
  <li>Run Omea Reader</li>
  <li>Press the <strong>subscribe</strong> button</li>
  <li>Enter the URL of your personal account's RSS feed, your jc number and password</li>
  <%= image_tag("support/installation/omea/rss_feed_subscribe.png") %>
  <li>Right click your new Posts folder, and choose notify me</li>
  <%= image_tag("support/installation/omea/rss_feed_notify.png") %>
  <li>Choose your preferred notification options, then press OK</li>
  <%= image_tag("support/installation/omea/rss_feed_notify_options.png") %>
  <p><span class='ui-state-highlight'><span class="ui-icon ui-icon-info" style="float: left; margin-right: .3em;"></span>If you select <strong>Show Desktop Alert</strong>, Omea Reader will show notifications when new posts are made matching your notification preferences</span></p>
  <%= image_tag("support/installation/omea/rss_feed_notify_alert.png") %>
</ol>


<a id="notification_setup_mac_os_x"></a>
<h3>Mac OS X</h3>
<h4>RSS Growler</h4>
<p class='ui-state-highlight'><span class="ui-icon ui-icon-info" style="float: left; margin-right: .3em;"></span>This guide is written based on Growl version 1.2.2 and on RSS Growler version 1.3</p>
<ol>
  <li>Download Growl from <%= link_to 'http://growl.info/downloads', 'http://growl.info/downloads' %></li>
  <li>Install Growl</li>
  <li>Download RSS Growler from <%= link_to 'http://osiris.laya.com/projects/RSSGrowler/', 'http://osiris.laya.com/projects/RSSGrowler/' %></li>
  <li>Unzip RSS Growler</li>
  <li>Drag RSS Growler into your Application folder</li>
  <%= image_tag("support/installation/rss_growler/drag_into_application_folder.png") %>
  <li>Open RSS Growler from your Applications folder</li>
  <li>Modify your RSS Growler Preferences</li>
  <%= image_tag("support/installation/rss_growler/preferences.png") %>
  <li>Subscribe to your personal account's RSS feed</li>
  <%= image_tag("support/installation/rss_growler/subscribe.png") %>
  <p><span class='ui-state-highlight'><span class="ui-icon ui-icon-info" style="float: left; margin-right: .3em;"></span>You will now recieve notifications about posts matching your notification preferences</span></p>
  <%= image_tag("support/installation/rss_growler/notification.png") %>
</ol>

<a id="notification_preferences"></a>
<h2>Setting Your Notification Preferences</h2>
<p>
Notifications are provided based on the following:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>If a post is made, and you haven't liked or disliked tags associated with it, then you will be notified of it.</li>
  <li>If a post is made, and you have liked tags associated with it, then you will always be notified of it.</li>
  <li>If a post is made, and you have disliked tags associated with it, but haven't liked any tags associated with it, then you won't be notified of it.</li>
</ul>

<p>We expect to refine this system further in the future.</p>

<p>When viewing a Post, you can like or dislike the tags associated with it. In the following image, you can see a post and its associate tags.</p>
<%= image_tag("support/post_notification_tags.png") %>

<p>If you wanted to hear more about ideas related to the ieee, then you would press <strong>like</strong> on the tag <strong>ieee</strong></p>

<p>If you wanted to hear less about ideas related to robotics, then you would press <strong>dislike</strong> on the tag <strong>robot</strong></p>

<p>You can later alter your existing notification preferences from your edit-profile page.</p>
<%= image_tag("support/edit_notification_preferences.png") %>

<p>Pressing <strong>forget</strong> removes your existing preference for that tag.</p>
</div>
